@page "/about"

<div class="container py-4">
    <h1>About Rota</h1>

    <p>
        Rota is a lightweight rota and shift management application designed to help teams
        manage schedules, shifts, reminders and absences with minimal fuss. It was built
        with Blazor and modern .NET technologies to provide a responsive, single-page
        application experience.
    </p>

    <h2>Support & Suggestions</h2>
    <p>
        If you have questions, need assistance, or would like to suggest a feature, please
        reach out to the project maintainer:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:support@rota.example">support@rota.example</a></li>
        <li>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/andyellingson/Rota" target="_blank">https://github.com/andyellingson/Rota</a> (issues & suggestions)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Feedback</h2>
    <p>
        We welcome feedback on usability and feature requests. Opening an issue on the
        GitHub repository is the best way to report bugs or request enhancements so they
        can be tracked and prioritized.
    </p>

    <p class="text-muted small mt-4">© Rota</p>
</div>
